<TITLE> Huda gets bail; Abbas, Babar detention illegal: HC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)  The High Court on Thursday granted two months interim bail to former communication minister Nazmul Huda in a corruption case, and declared the detention of former ministers Mirza Abbas and Lutfozzaman Babar illegal. A HC bench of justices Md. Arayesuddin and Abu Tariq awarded bail based on a petition made by the BNP leader in the case involving newspaper Khoborer Antorale. The hearing on behalf of Nazmul Huda was carried out by senior advocate Fazlul Karim, while advocate Abdul Aziz for the Anticorruption Commission opposed the bail petition. Shafiqul Islam, ACC deputy director filed the case against Nazmul and his wife advocate Sigma Huda on March 21 last year. A trial court year sentenced Huda to seven years imprisonment and Sigma to three years on Aug 27. Meanwhile, the bench of justices Tariq-ul-Hakim and Farah Mahbub declared illegal the detention of former ministers Mirza Abbas and Lutfozzaman Babor. The court directed the government to set them free if the are not accused in any other cases. Advocate Ahsanul Karim move the petitions of Abbas and Babar. Another HC bench of justices Musa Khaled and Md Emdadul Haque acquitted former BNP whip Prof Md Shahjahan Miah in an extortion case. A trial court sentenced the former lawmaker from Chapainawabganj to five years imprisonment in the case on July 7 last year. bdnew
